- Record user activities in your aws account

- enabled by default

- records events such as creation, deletion, modifications of resources

- logs API calls that are made in your aws account

- ssh/rdp into ec2 instance, cloudtrail doesn't log that

- by default cloudtrail keeps logs for 90days

- to keep longer than 90days, we create a trail and by default the data is encrypted

- by default cloudtrail logs multi-region

- The logs are stored in the cloudtrail folder

- can take up to 15mins for cloudtrail to see the api log

WHAT GETS LOGGED

- who
- when
- what and where
- source IP
- request parameters
- Response
